<item>
            <title>[SPR-1028] dropDatabaseSchema does not work with Postgres</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-1028</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;LocalSessionFactoryBean.dropDatabaseSchema() does not work with Postgresql if the schema is already there and you change a name&lt;br/&gt;
in the table names. This happens because once a command fails postgres won&apos;t process further commands in the same transaction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a workaround, simply use autocommit=true in executeSchemaScript.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are other problems tought. For example, if you change a foreign key name in the mapping file, dropping won&apos;t work because the old foreign key won&apos;t be removed (and thus the tables won&apos;t be removed). I guess this is a Hibernate problem, thought, that should generate a DROP TABLE xxx CASCADE instead of a simple DROP TABLE xxx&lt;/p&gt;</description>
