                            <comment id="13547" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Mon, 13 Jun 2005 05:38:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, it&apos;s probably generally advisable to execute DDL scripts with autoCommit=true. Hibernate&apos;s own SchemaUpdate does that too. Most databases don&apos;t support transactions for DDL in the first place, and LocalSessionFactoryBean catches failing DDL statements anyway...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, I&apos;ve changed LocalSessionFactoryBean accordingly, for both Hibernate 2.1 and Hibernate 3.0.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The actual drop statements etc are generated by Hibernate, so that one is indeed a Hibernate problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
